I have an embedded flash object in a page using the flash macro:

{flash:file=^flexChart.swf|width=800|height=100}

It would be really nice if the wysiwyg editor was able to show the size of this object and allow it to be resized.  As it is now, sizing has to be done trial and error style since all the users sees is the above line when editing.

It would be nice to extend the editor to support plugins that cooperate with the editor in a manner similar to an image.   That is, a version of the object is shown with resize handles instead of a cryptic line of text.  The above works 'OK' for developers but is really hard for regular or casual users.  For flash objects, it would be nice to actually show the flash object in the editor as it should adapt nicely to resizing on the fly.

