I use the following CSS to ensure that the navigation bar on the left hand side of my pages is not included in printed output (via the print page feature of the browser):

{style:media=print}
.navbar { display: none }
{style}

That aspect works fine.  However, this styling is not picked up by the Export to PDF/Word feature of Confluence, with the result that all such output is unusable (because the navbar takes up half the width of the page).

As an aside, I used to use the {hide-if:display=printable} macro to disable the navbar when clicking on the Print link in Confluence.  However, the print link seems to have disappeared after our Confluence instance was upgraded to 2.8.1 and the {hide-if:display=printable} macro no longer appears to have an effect.

Regards
Kevin

