External images included in a page are double htmlEncoded which means that any external image urls with non standard characters don't work.

For example: 

{code:none}
!http://chart.apis.google.com/chart?cht=p3&chd=t:60,40&chs=250x100&chl=Hello\|World!
{code}

becomes 
